Subjects

            Climate changeClimate sciences

Key points

                Events exhibiting spatial, temporal, and multivariate compounding interactions drove devastating floods and wildfires in Asia and North America in 2025.


                Severe flooding in North and South America resulted from heavy precipitation following both anomalous wet spells (temporal compounding) and dry spells (preconditioning).


                Heat events compounded with biological extremes to damage marine ecosystems near Australia, and with drought to stress food and energy systems in Mesopotamia.

